(102, 1, '2011-01-27 00:38:39', '2011-01-27 00:38:39', '            Hi, my name is Marcos, i’m a Spanish guy and i’m writing you from Dublin, Ireland. I’m currently finishing my studies before going back home for good. However, before that happens i would like to share some experiences with you, giving you an overview of how my life was here during the last months.\n\n            Sincerely it wasn’t difficult for me to take the decision to leave Spain. In those days i didn''t have a job and the English language was required in every enterview i went to. My level, how everybody can guess, wasn’t high enough to get any job. Why i decided to <a title="Learn English Dublin / Ireland" href="http://www.ulearn.ie/learn_english_dublin">learn english in Ireland</a> is a very interesting question!! I think the fact that a relative of mine was living here for a long time was decisive. The first four days i was living with a friend of my relative, a period of time i used to look for an apartment, which wasn’t very difficult, (the range of accomodation in Dlublin is really wide!!). Once i had a place to leave my stuff i started looking for a school, what was very tough due to the fact that Dublin is a very spread out city!!! Eventually, the way i found the school was quite interesting: i was shopping in Tesco, (the supermarket near my house), when i saw a Spanish girl who recommended me a school just in the heart of the city. To be Frank, the fact of starting to study at school was a tipping point for me, due to the amount of students i met, all of them<a href="http://dev.wp/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/foto-22.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-22" title="Foto 2" src="http://dev.wp/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/foto-22.jpg?w=300" alt="" width="350" height="301" /></a><a href="http://dev.wp/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/foto-21.jpg"></a> from different countries. (Can you imagine how many people there are doing <a title="English course(s) Dublin" href="http://www.ulearn.ie/english_courses_dublin">english couses in Dlubin</a>???). That’s why i think you should enrol at a school just in the moment you arrive. That will open you a lot of possibilities.\n\n           Then guys, i hope this piece of information can be useful for you. See u soon!!\n\n            MARCOSSS', 'STUDENTS THROUGHOUT THE WORLD', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '16-revision', '', '', '2011-01-27 00:38:39', '2011-01-27 00:38:39', '', 16, 'http://dev.wp/?p=102', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
