(108, 1, '2011-01-27 01:43:36', '2011-01-27 01:43:36', 'So there i was!! My first week in another country, without a home or friends. I would be lying if i said it was an easy way at the beginning. However all changed my first day at school. Running the School were three guys, all of them young, who gave me a hand with everything , from looking for a bike to moving around Dublin to translating my CV into English and looking for a job. Here you have, as i said in my last article, the important of searching for an <a title="English School Dublin" href="http://www.ulearn.ie/english_school_dubln" target="_blank"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-37" title="FOTO 3" src="http://dev.wp/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/foto-31.jpg?w=300" alt="" width="231" height="173" />english school in Dublin</a>, instead of leaving your country in haste, just like i did.\n\nBefore coming to Ireland i thought my English level was acceptable, but when i started in pre-intermediate level i realized how far i still had to go.\n\nMay be somebody is thinking…”What about your class mates???” Simply Amazing people. That’s the reason for the title, we were an interesting group: two Koreans, two Italians, three Spanish guys, one Japanese girl, two Mexicans and a Russian girl who arrived later. Could you imagine how difficult it was to communicate between us?? However you realise how important it is to have a multicultural class, above all for the training of your ears.\n\nI tried all the ways to learn English back in my country: private classes, on my own, at the national <a title="english language school" href="http://www.ulearn.ie/english_courses_ulearn" target="_blank">english languages school</a>,… and to my mind the Only way to learn properly English is living in a native English country.\n\nSo See u next week guys!! If anybody has any question, i’ll be pleased to answer them!!!\n\nMarcosss', 'AN INTERESTING GROUP (in my English school, Dublin)', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '34-revision', '', '', '2011-01-27 01:43:36', '2011-01-27 01:43:36', '', 34, 'http://dev.wp/?p=108', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
