(184, 1, '2011-04-01 12:45:04', '2011-04-01 12:45:04', '<img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-151" title="Map" src="http://dev.wp/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/P2200368-300x225.jpg" alt="" width="180" height="135" />We don''t have clases on the <a title="English School Dublin" href="http://www.ulearn.ie/english_school_dubln" target="_blank">english school Dublin</a> on weekends, so we tend to visit others cities or towns.\r\nA good option was <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Howth" target="_blank">Howth</a>, a little fishing village on a hill surrounded by cliffs. It’s at 15 kilometres from the centre of Dublin.\r\n\r\nSo, we left the Conolly Station at 10.45am, and we spent 20 minutes to arrive to Howth. Out of the station, we saw a map where were 4 indicated routes. We decided to make the long one, which goes around the whole peninsula.\r\n\r\nJust when we started to walk, we saw the Ireland’s Eye, an islet near Howth. Unfortunately the weather wasn’t very good so, we couldn’t see it very well. We noticed that in summer there are some boats for arrive there and visit the monastery’s runes.\r\n\r\n<img class="size-medium wp-image-152 alignleft" src="http://dev.wp/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/P2200332-225x300.jpg" alt="" width="203" height="270" />\r\n\r\nWe walked along the cliffs, through a narrow and muddy path (It’d rained the night before). We came across a little beach and we saw the lighthouse. We were walking during 2 hours so we decided to stop and to eat some food we’d taken from home. After this short break, we continued with our route. We were surprised when we had to cross the golf course, following some white stones indicating the path.\r\n\r\nThe route finishes in the same place where it starts, so we arrived at the station, and in front of it, there was a little market. Then, we went to the port, where we could see some seals waiting for some fish that people were giving them.\r\n\r\nWe were so tired, and we had cold so we entered to a bar with views on the port to get a tea. Then we returned to Dublin. We arrived there at 7pm and, like every Sunday, we went to get a beer in a Pub in Dame Street to close the week with a good concert and start again another week of <a title="English Classes Dublin / Ireland" href="http://www.ulearn.ie/quality_english_courses_dublin" target="_blank">English classes Dublin</a>', 'VISITING HOWTH', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '150-revision-6', '', '', '2011-04-01 12:45:04', '2011-04-01 12:45:04', '', 150, 'http://dev.wp/?p=184', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
