(240, 1, '2011-04-19 23:03:11', '2011-04-19 23:03:11', 'One of all the good things of <a href="http://www.ulearn.ie/learn_english_dublin" target="_blank">study English Dublin</a> is that you can know people of other countries and cultures, and you can learn a lot with this.\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;"><img class="size-medium wp-image-241 alignleft" title="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://dev.wp/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/P3270870-300x225.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="225" /></span>The other day, after some of our Korean classmates of the <a href="http://www.ulearn.ie/english_school_dublin" target="_blank">English School Dublin</a> organized a Korean dinner\r\n\r\nfor us. They cooked <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bulgogi" target="_blank">Bulgogi</a> and rice, then we had to put them in a leaf of lettuce with a little bit of an spicy sauce, made a ball with all and ate it, putting all the ball in the mouth on the same time. It was really good!\r\n\r\nIn <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Korea" target="_blank">Korea</a>, it’s very common to eat rice at all the meals, including breakfast, the same with the soup.\r\n\r\nThere are some <a href="http://www.yelp.ie/c/dublin/korean" target="_blank">Korean Restaurants in Dublin</a>.', 'Korean Dinner, with my classmates in Dublin.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'korean-dinner-with-my-classmates-in-dublin', '', '', '2013-04-11 15:59:51', '2013-04-11 15:59:51', '', 0, 'http://dev.wp/?p=240', 0, 'post', '', 0),
